		<p class="main_h1"><a name="upc">Upcoming</a></p>

		<p class="main_h2"><a name="mat">Matsuri</a></p>
		<pre>Our annual spring festival. More details to come.</pre>
		<p class="main_h2">Date: Friday, April 28th, 2006<br>
		Time: 5:00-9:00 PM<br>
		Location: Low Plaza</p>
		<o class="top"><a class="Main" href="#top"Top</a></p>

		<p class="main_h1"><a name="rec">Recent</a></p>
  
		<p class="main_h2"><a name="cih">Curry in a Hurry</a></p>
		<pre>Love curry? Come check out CJS's annual Curry in a Hurry 
featuring curries from all around the world. 
CJS, AAA, CSC, Liga Filipina, KPL, HKSSS,  TSA, SEAL,
TASA, PDP, and VSA are participating, 
providing you with curry, refreshments and dessert.

It's just $5 for as much curry as you can handle. 
Green tea, other drinks, dessert, rice, and more are all included. 
It all starts at 7pm in Lerner C555, and goes until we run out.

And come vote which club receives the right to the title: Imperial Sovereign of Curry!</pre>

		<p class="main_h2">Date: Friday, February 24th, 2006<br>
		Time: 7:00 PM<br>
		Location: Lerner C555</p>
		<o class="top"><a class="Main" href="#top"Top</a></p>


		<p class="main_h2"><a name="ori">Origami Night!</a></p>
		<pre>Come hang out with the board of CJS this friday, enjoy the FREE FOOD 
and have fun creating your own origami creations, which one of our 
OCMs guarantees to be quite the adventure!</pre>

		<p class="main_h2">Date: Friday, February 17th, 2006<br>
		Time: 7:00 PM<br>
		Location: Satow (5th fl. Lerner)</p>
		<o class="top"><a class="Main" href="#top"Top</a></p>


		<p class="main_h2"><a name="sgm">Second General Membership Meeting</a></p>
		<pre>Come talk with the board and mingle with other Japan Society 
Members. Featuring free food, games, and entertainment, as well as 
announcements of future events.

Also showcasing what may be our best game as of yet: 

              Ningen Tataki -- HUMAN Whack-A-Mole! 

You won't want to miss it!</pre>		

		<p class="main_h2">Date: Monday, January 30, 2006<br>
        	Time: 7:00PM<br>
        	Location: Satow (5th fl. Lerner)</p>
		<p class="top"><a class="main" href="#top">Top</a></p>

		<p class="main_h2"><a name="gsn">Game Show Night</a></p>
		<pre>CJS "Zany Japanese Game Shows"-inspired Study Break

Been living on fourth floor of Butler? Want to take a break from the
numerous problem sets, papers, projects and exams but don't know
where to go?

Come to our study break Monday night for FREE FOOD and crazy
Japanese-tv-show-inspired GAMES brought to you by our board!</pre>
		<p class="main_h2">Date: Monday, November 14, 2005<br>
      		Time: 9:00PM<br>
      		Location: Lerner E568</p>
		<p class="top"><a class="main" href="#top">Top</a></p>
	 
		<p class="main_h2"><a name="mvn">Movie Night</a></p>
		<pre>This year, CJS presents the quintessential Japanese horror movie,
INFECTION. INFECTION makes blatant use of the most stereotypical
Japanese horror movie setting--the hospital. However, the movie
proves to be refreshingly frightening to even those who may find
the use of this archetypal setting tacky. For those yet unfamiliar 
to the Japanese horror genre, INFECTION will be sure to give you a 
very shocking introduction to the Japanese sense of horror.</pre>
      	<p class="main_h2">Date: Saturday, October 27, 2005<br>
			Time: 7:30PM<br>
			Location: Lerner E569</p>
	  	<p class="top"><a class="main" href="#top">Top</a></p>
	  
	  	<p class="main_h2"><a name="sxs">Sexy Sushi</a></p>
        <pre>Come and join us for our annual Sexy Sushi Night.
We're buying 50% more sushi-ingredients this year to keep you guys well fed! 
So create-your-own, eat-all-you-like and party with us all evening. 
You're welcome to dress sexily - or not! - but keep it classy.
		
The sexiest dressed person will win a $50 gift certificate to East.
			
Come eat sushi! . . . Or just come.</pre>
        <p class="main_h2">Date: Saturday, October 22, 2005<br>
          Time: 6:00PM<br>
          Location: Lerner Party Space</p>
		<p class="top"><a class="main" href="#top">Top</a></p>		  

		<p class="main_h2"><a name="nyc">CJS Tour of NYC</a></p>
        <pre>Once again, CJS will be holding a tour of Japanese "hot spots"
according to the knowledgeable Miss Teriha Hashimoto, which will
include Shobo-ji Zen Temple, Urasenke (tea house), Book Off! and
the inevitable St. Marks area!  Sign up since space is limited, and
be ready to sightsee and shop for practically anything
Japan-related! As a treat, CJS will provide you with a free pastry
from Beard Papa's Cream Puff!</pre>
        <p class="main_h2">Date: Saturday, October 1, 2005<br>
          Time: 10:00AM<br>
          Location: 116th Gates</p>
		<p class="top"><a class="main" href="#top">Top</a></p>
		
		<p class="main_h2"><a name="fgm">First General Membership Meeting</a></p>
        <pre>Come meet the board and mingle with other Japan Society Members.
Featuring free food, games, and entertainment, as well as announcements on future events.
		
Got rice? If not, you can win a rice cooker!
		
Get the <a class="main" href="flyers/cjs_genmeetflyer.pdf" target="_blank">flyer</a></pre>
		<p class="main_h2">Date: Saturday, September 24, 2005<br>
        	Time: 7:30PM<br>
        	Location: Lerner E569</p>
